It’s that time of the year again, where people relax and enjoy their holidays through a variety of activities.  Locals and visitors are in for a treat with a packed programme of seaside activities during the annual uMhlanga Summer Festival, taking place from 14 to 23 December. The festival launch by uMhlanga Tourism, was held on 21 November under the theme ‘Colours of Africa”.   Highlights include the Miss and Mr uMhlanga pageant and the Carols under the Stars concert. The festival has been running for more than ten years, with the aim to provide a range of fun-filled activities during the festive season.